Cortosis weave is a descriptor for equipment that had been crafted utilizing cortosis ore. This is traditionally put into swords or other melee weapons but could also be fashioned into armor or other gear. Cortosis weave is employed primarily because it made the weapon able to withstand lightsaber blows. Weapons needs very little cortosis to be effective but armor requires a substantially larger amount. The greater quantity provides an additional benefit to wearers though- a lightsaber would deactivate after contact is made with cortosis armor. Cortosis is extremely rare though and, thus, extremely expensive, resulting in few weapons and armor made with it.

The tip of the Force Pike is a vibro-edged head with a stun module that could knock a full-grown Wookiee unconscious using a concentrated nerve impulse similar to that featured in the stun setting of a blaster rifle. The impulse works by overloading the central nervous system, effectively knocking the victim unconscious. When the vibro-edge is set to maximum it could rip through steel bulkheads and easily dismember most organic beings. The control settings and power generator are located at the pike's grip. It should be noted that Force Pikes are not related to the Force.

Cortosis is extremely rare though and, thus, extremely expensive, resulting in few weapons and armor made with it.

The BlasTech DL-22 Blaster Pistol is designed as a response to the MerrSonn DD6 weapon. The gun's barrel used a higher-grade focusing crystal to increase the damage dealt by the weapon's blasts, at the expense of the gun's stun setting. The DL-22 is held in high regard by those who prefer to customize their weapons.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.
BlasTech DL-22

The CR-2 blaster pistol is a basic yet durable heavy blaster pistol used by the Royal Naboo Security Forces. They are famous for being able to deflect off certain surfaces yet penetrate armor.

The CR-2 blaster was a basic blaster design created by the little-known Corellian Arms corporation, and was the first mass-produced version of the modern blaster weapon introduced on Naboo. The CR-2 primarily fired bolts of charged plasma energy, but a secondary firing mode allowed the weapon to discharge electrical bolts capable of stunning most living targets. The CR-2 pistol became an antique on most Core Worlds long before the Naboo Security Forces adopted it as the standard-issue sidearm for its Security Guards and police officers.

The BlasTech Industries DL-44 heavy blaster pistol is a powerful sidearm created for the use in the currently raging Galactic Civil War.

It has found some use by the Rebel Alliance on account of its ability to consistently penetrate stormtrooper armor. It was outlawed by the Empire because of this. As a side effect, however, it has a somewhat slow rate of fire and uses about four times as much energy as a standard blaster, exhausting its magazine in about 50 shots. It weighs about 1.3 kg. A unique feature of the DL-44 is the vibration system built into the handgrip. A small stud in the grip begins to pulse gently to alert the user when the weapon's remaining energy is sufficient for five shots or fewer.

The KYD-21 is a blaster pistol favored by bounty hunters and assassins during the decades leading up to the establishment of the Galactic Empire.

This compact blaster was crafted from hadrium alloy, and features a ridged handgrip with guardless trigger. The muzzle features a brake to absorb the emitter flash, and both the igniter pin and blaster gas loading port are located on the grip beneath the barrel. The pistol is noted for its impressive stopping power, despite its small size, and, though expensive, became popular amongst assassins for its subtlety.

Holdout blasters (also hold-out blaster) are small, palm-sized blasters that could be easily concealed inside a sleeve. Because of their small size, holdout blasters usually can only fire two shots before expending their power cells. They saw widespread use in weapon-restricted areas and were commonly found in the possession of undercover agents, gamblers and other scoundrels, or nobles seeking to protect themselves. They were sometimes carried by more lethal characters for back-up firepower. Iella Wessiri Antilles, Mara Jade Skywalker, and Han Solo are among the many to use holdout blasters.

This holdout blaster pistol, sometimes known as a scout blaster, is a standard-issue weapon used by the scout troopers of the Galactic Empire. Clone scout troopers of the 41st Elite Legion were also known to carry these weapons during the latter stages of the Clone Wars.

This compact, one-handed blaster is fitted with a side-mounted targeting scope and phase amplifier, and featured a miniature gas cell on the rear. The weapon had a short-range barrel. Scout troopers commonly carry these weapons in a boot holster. Because scout troopers wore padded gloves, the pistol has a pressure-sensitive stock rather than a trigger. Bandoliers, were medium to large items of utilitarian clothing that the owner could wear around their left or right shoulder down across their torso, or as a large belt. Normally worn by military or paramilitary forces as well as mercenaries and others who needed large supplies of ammunition, bandoliers consisted of many ammunition pouches sewn together or snapped to a belt. Though typically used to carry extra ammunition for blaster-type and other ranged weaponry, bandoliers could also carry grenades, supplies of synthrope, and other sorts of items useful on the battlefield or in covert operations.
